main_docs (["main":({"This handler is meant to simulate the changing of an object's\"state\", such as melting, grinding, etc.  In reality, rather thanchanging the source object, the transform() method clones acompletely new object, based on the internal lookup table; it isthe caller's responsibility to dest the source object and put thenew one in its place.<p>The handler's lookup table is stored in a series of files:any files in /obj/state_change ending in .dat will be addedto the table when the handler is loaded.  See /include/state_change.hfor field definitions.  The data files are loaded by the datahandler, and can contain fancy things like expressions and functionpointers.",}),"author":({"Jeremy",}),"see":({"/include/state_change.h","/obj/handlers/data.c",}),])
